# Netlify redirects — URL rewrites for the FEL site

# Staging-specific robots.txt — block all crawlers on fel-staging.netlify.app
# Production (fiordlandexpeditions.co.nz) gets the default robots.txt.
# Uses Netlify's documented full-URL form for host-based redirects: the
# hostname goes in the from-side rather than as a Host= condition (which
# Netlify silently ignores). The 200! force flag is required because
# /robots.txt exists as a real file in the build; without it Netlify
# serves the file directly and the rewrite is bypassed.
https://fel-staging.netlify.app/robots.txt  /robots-staging.txt  200!

# Guest Content Hub — clean, thumb-typable URLs for vessel QR codes
# and guest-facing print collateral
/gch       /pages/guest-content-hub.html   200
/share     /pages/guest-content-hub.html   200

# Preserve deep-links to specific tabs via query string
